<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="590">3.2.1. Transferring commissions to other manufacturers</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can transfer commissions that were saved for one manufacturer to others. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Transferring commissions from one manufacturer to another:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Manufacturers</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the manufacturer with the commissions that you want to transfer.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Commissions</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Copy commission to other manufacturers</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the <strong>commissions</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the <strong>manufacturers</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Copy commission</strong>.<br>
→ The commissions will be transferred to the selected manufacturers.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="620">3.3. Deleting manufacturers</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to delete manufacturers, all links between items and manufacturers must be deleted first. Use the <strong>Item group function</strong> and proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting manufacturer links:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Manufacturer</strong> filter, select the manufacturer from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>ALL</strong> in the <strong>Active</strong> filter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong>.<br>
→ All items linked with this manufacturer will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Select all</strong> in the header of the item overview.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Item group function</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Item group function</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Global</strong> area, activate the option <strong>Manufacturers</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the empty option from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Execute</strong>.<br>
→ The manufacturer links will be deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Then delete the manufacturer.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting manufacturers:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Manufacturers</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong> in the line of a manufacturer.<br>
→ The <strong>Delete manufacturers</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ The manufacturer will be deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="630">4. Managing barcodes</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Barcodes such as GTIN, ISBN, UPC and QR are used to identify items in plentymarkets. Create any number of barcodes and link these barcodes with your item variations. In addition, set up GTIN numbering to generate barcodes automatically and make these barcodes available when linking them with variations.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="640">4.1. Creating barcodes</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Create barcodes of different types for your item variations.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a barcode:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Barcode</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New barcode</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>New barcode</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the type. Pay attention to the information given in table 7.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the barcode.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate one or multiple referrers.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
