<h2 id="910">7. Creating price calculations</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Price calculations allow you to customise and graduate prices for different customer classes and referrers. In the <strong>Price calculation</strong> menu, you create individual variations for prices which will then be available in the <strong>Settings</strong> tab of a variation. Price calculations will automatically be taken into account for saved prices. Use the variation group function to set up price calculations for multiple item variations at once.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a price calculation:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Calculation</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New price calculation</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>New price calculation</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong>.<br>
→ The new price calculation will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in table 12.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
