<h2 id="690">8. Managing units</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Units are used to specify the content of your items. Create units in accordance with the ISO code or individual units and add translated texts, if needed.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="700">8.1. Creating units</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you need other units than the units available in the system, create additional ones.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a unit:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Units</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Create new unit</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a position if needed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The new unit will be created and displayed in the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="710">8.2. Editing units</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can edit existing units and add translations in different languages.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a unit:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Units</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the unit.<br>
→ The tab of the unit will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in table 13.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
