<div class="paragraph">
<p>Generate labels directly from the template or with the <strong>Labels</strong> function of an item or variation. You also can use the plentymarkets Client and the available processes to <a href="/en/basics/automation/processes/procedures#150">generate labels</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Generating a label using a template:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Labels</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the template.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the order ID.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Preview</strong>.<br>
→ A PDF file with the labels for the items of this order will be generated.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Generate labels for items by clicking on <strong>Labels</strong> in the toolbar of an item. Generate labels for item variations in the same way by clicking on <strong>Labels</strong> in the tab of a variation.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="790">10. Setting up flags</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Items can be flagged. Flags can help you with organising and sorting your items. Flags are activated in the item and are displayed in the item overview. You can find flagged items quickly in plentymarkets by using the filters <strong>Flag&nbsp;1</strong> and <strong>Flag&nbsp;2</strong>. By default, flags are named after their ID. To rename flags, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Renaming a flag:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Flags</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the line <strong>Name</strong>, enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Learn how to use flags in the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#810">Adding flags to items</a> chapter.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">11. Creating categories</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets 7, you use <a href="/en/item/managing-categories">categories</a> for organising and managing your items. We recommend that you create all categories and subcategories at once. This will help you to structure and understand your product portfolio.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a category:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Categories</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New category</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Create new category</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the category type.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If you activate <strong>Subcategory</strong>, then select the category that should include the new subcategory.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create</strong>.<br>
→ The new category will be created and displayed in the category tree.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Alternatively, create a category by clicking on <strong>New category</strong> when creating a new item in the <strong>Item » Edit item » New item</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>New categories are assigned the type <strong>Item</strong> by default. The settings required for categories of the <strong>Item</strong> type are described below. These settings are different from the category settings for the <strong>Content</strong> type. For further information about the remaining settings, refer to the **﻿ Managing categories&gt;&gt; page of the manual.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a category of the "Item" type:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Categories</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the category.<br>
→ The <strong>settings</strong> tab will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Under <strong>Client (store)</strong>, select one or multiple clients.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a template from the <strong>Template page</strong> drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a template from the <strong>Template list</strong> drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a template from the <strong>Template product</strong> drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Changing the category type</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If a category is already linked to items and you change the category type from <strong>Item</strong> to <strong>Content</strong>, then these links will not be deleted automatically. However, the category will no longer be displayed for the item.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Learn more about linking items to categories in the following video tutorial:</p>
</div>
<div class="videoblock">
<div class="content">
<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/122644529" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="15">12. Creating a pattern for new variation numbers</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Variation numbers are assigned automatically when you create <strong>Default</strong> items or variations. You specify the patterns of new variation numbers in the <strong>System » Item » Settings</strong> menu. Proceed as described below to specify the pattern for creating new variation numbers.</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Configure the settings <strong>Prefix for new variation numbers</strong> and <strong>Next variation number</strong>. Pay attention to the information given in table 15.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
