<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="610">14.2. Linking manufacturers</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Link manufacturers either when <a href="/en/item/managing-items#20">creating a Default item</a> or in the existing <strong>Default</strong> item’s <strong>Global</strong> tab.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking manufacturers:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Edit item</strong> in the line of a <strong>Default</strong> item.<br>
→ The <strong>Default</strong> item’s <strong>Global</strong> tab will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Basic settings</strong> area, select the <strong>manufacturer</strong> from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The manufacturer will be linked with the <strong>Default</strong> item.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="45">14.3. Changing a Default item’s settings for markets</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Multi-Channel</strong> tab, change the settings for the markets <a href="/en/omni-channel/multi-channel/amazon">Amazon</a>, <a href="/en/omni-channel/multi-channel/ebay">eBay</a> and <a href="/en/omni-channel/multi-channel/neckermann-at">Neckermann.at</a>. Furthermore, link your categories to the categories of markets. The settings in this area are for the topic <a href="/en/omni-channel/multi-channel">Multi-Channel</a> and are described on the markets' pages.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
