<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="60">14.5. Searching and replacing item texts</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Search &amp; replace</strong> menu, you search for item texts in the database and replace the results with new texts.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching and replacing item texts:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Search &amp; replace</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the database field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the text into the search field. The field is case-sensitive.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the new text into <strong>Replace by</strong> field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong>.<br>
→ The number of relevant items will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Replace all</strong>.<br>
→ All texts will be replaced by the new texts.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="70">14.6. Activate free text fields</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Add free text fields to the detailed view of a <strong>Default</strong> item. Customers can then enter values into the free text fields, such as an additional request or dimensions. First, define the free text fields.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Defining free text fields:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Free text fields</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a field name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the data type. Pay attention to the information given in table 19.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the number of characters.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<caption class="title">Table 19. Defining free text fields</caption>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 33.3333%;">
