<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="140">14.11. Displaying item statistics</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Statistics</strong> tab, you can create different statistics for the <strong>Default</strong> item. These statistics e.g. let you analyse the <strong>Default</strong> item’s revenue according to various criteria. For further information, refer to the <a href="/en/basics/statistics/item-statistics">Item statistics</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="150">14.12. Adding tags to items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you made your <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/tags">tags</a> available for the <strong>Item</strong> menu, you can add tags to items.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding a tag:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Global</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the text field in the <strong>tags</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the tag name. Alternatively, select a tag from the list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The tag is added to the item.<br>
→ The item can be found in the item overview by applying the tag filter.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="810">14.13. Adding flags to Default items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Add up to two flags to a <strong>Default</strong> item. Learn how to rename flags in the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#790">Setting up flags</a> chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding a flag to a Default item:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Default</strong> item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the greyed out button in the toolbar on the right.<br>
→ A drop-down menu will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a flag from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
