<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="280">17.6. Specifying costs</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Costs</strong> area, you specify the VAT rate and the variation’s purchase price. You also enter additional costs such as costs for transportation and storage. These entries are used for calculating your sales prices. For further information about price calculation, refer to <a href="/en/item/managing-items#910">Creating price calculations</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Specifying the costs of the main variation:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Default</strong> item.<br>
→ The <strong>Settings</strong> tab of the main variation will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the information given in table 29 and carry out the settings in the <strong>Costs</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
