<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The period in days that the stock of a specific variation will suffice until the next reorder. This value is relevant for calculating reorder proposals. A standard value that could be used for the stock turnover is 14 days. Once the variation has reached the reorder level, the value entered will be used for calculating the quantity of items that need to be reordered. In other words, the quantity suggested for reorder would be sufficient for the following 14 days. If no value is entered, the stock turnover (in days) is not taken into account for calculating the reorder date.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Maximum stock</strong></p></td>
