<h3 id="360">20.3. Filtering by categories</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Category</strong> tab, you can search for items of a specific category only.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Filtering items by category:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the search area, click on the <strong>Categories</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on a category to display all of the items in this category.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Alternatively, expand a category and click on a subcategory.<br>
→ All items found will be displayed in the item overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to search for items in all of the categories again.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deactivating the category search:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
