<h3 id="385">20.6. Setting up the search index</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A search index is needed in order for items to be found more easily during an item search in the plentymarkets back end and in the online store. The search index will be set up automatically when new items are created. The search index will be updated the night after you imported the items and will be available the next day. In the <strong>System » Item » Search index</strong> menu, you can manually start updating the search index. In the <strong>Item catalogue</strong> tab, you can see how many items are included in the search index. In the <strong>Item properties</strong> tab, you can see how many items with properties are included in the search index. The following table explains the settings in the <strong>Search index</strong> menu.</p>
