<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="960">24.1. Setting up dynamic cross-selling</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In dynamic cross-selling, if items are purchased together, these additional items will be linked as cross-selling items with the main item automatically. These links will be visible in the online store the next day. Sales will be taken into account after activating this function. 10 dynamic cross-selling links are possible for each item. If there are more than 10 links, only the 10 best selling items will be displayed. You can manually delete the cross-selling links that were automatically generated. This is done in the item’s <strong>Cross-selling</strong> tab.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up dynamic cross-selling:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Online store » Basic settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>Use direct cross-selling</strong> for the <strong>Cross-selling</strong> option.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the option <strong>Yes</strong> for <strong>Dynamic cross-selling</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="970">24.2. Adding cross-selling items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Cross-selling</strong> tab of an item, create relations between an item and any number of similar items of your product range. You can also link accessories and replacement parts for the item. Use the <strong>Relation</strong> option to assign a category to the linked cross-selling item. You can then use template variables to determine the visibility in the online store. The relation of the linked cross-selling items can be changed at any time.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following requirements have to be met in order for direct <strong>cross-selling items</strong> to be displayed in your online store:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The category of the cross-selling item has to be activated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The items have to be visible in the online store.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding cross-selling items:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Cross-selling » Add item(s)</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place check marks next to the items that you want to add as cross-selling items.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the appropriate <strong>relation</strong>. Pay attention to the information given in table 41.<br>
→ The items will be added and displayed in the <strong>Cross-selling items</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
